    <stitle>8 SPEED, 9 SPEED, AND 13 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON SERIES - REMOVE - COUNTERSHAFT ASSEMBLIES</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="1">
        <title>COUNTERSHAFT ASSEMBLIES</title>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Except for the PTO gears, the left and right countershaft assemblies are identical and
                    disassembled in the same manner.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <para>Move the right countershaft assembly to the rear as far as possible so the front of the shaft can be
            removed from the case bore and moved to the center of the case (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f13018f1">Figure OTLNK>). Lift the assembly from the case and repeat the procedure for the
                left countershaft assembly.
            </hotlnk>
        </para>
        <figure id="f13018f1" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g13018f1" filename="../figg13/G13018F1.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 151. Remove Front of Shaft From Case Bore</caption>
        </figure>
    </svcproc>
